Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%sachet}, then season with @salt and @pepper. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine a good squeeze of lemon juice with the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper, then set your salad dressing aside.

Pat the @basa fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Lay the fish onto a lined baking tray. Spread the @fresh pesto{32%g} over the top of the fish, then sprinkle over half the lemon zest.

When the potatoes have 12 mins left, bake the fish on the middle shelf until cooked, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @sugar{1%tsp} for the salsa.

Once hot, add the tomato chunks and cook until just warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Gently stir in the garlic and remaining lemon zest and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Squeeze in some lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.

Taste and season again if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to your lemon dressing and toss to coat.

Transfer the pesto basa to your plates and spoon over the warm tomato salsa.

Serve with the rosemary potatoes and salad alongside. Enjoy!